Content: I like them simple but not too simple. Usually a small/medium house with a good amount of detail
All the grinding needed in survival to do stuff like that is really discouraging to me
Sure_ it's more rewarding_ but I don't like having to do all the tedious collecting

The furthest survival I think I've made it in recent times would be a custom Skyblock map me and a friend made. We wrote down 50 unique achievements in a book and saved it_ which really helped keep the pace up.
It was_ although it died off eventually ~~just like our friendship~~
